  "prompt": "How do I send 16-bit data to Arduino using Simulink?",
  "response": "To send 16-bit data to an Arduino using Simulink, you can use the \"Serial Transmit\" block provided in the Simulink Support Package for Arduino. Here's a step-by-step guide:\n\n1. **Install Simulink Support Package for Arduino**:\n   Ensure you have the Arduino Support Package installed. You can install it via MATLAB's Add-On Explorer.\n\n2. **Configure the Arduino**:\n   Connect your Arduino to your computer via USB and ensure it's recognized by the Arduino IDE. Note the COM port being used.\n\n3. **Create a Simulink Model**:\n   Open Simulink and create a new model.\n\n4. **Add the Serial Transmit Block**:\n   From the Simulink library browser, navigate to:\n   `Simulink Library > Simulink Support Package for Arduino Hardware > Common > Serial Transmit`\n\n5. **Set Up Serial Transmit Block**:\n   - Double-click the \"Serial Transmit\" block to configure it.\n   - Set the COM port to match the one your Arduino is using.\n   - Set the baud rate to a value consistent with your Arduino configuration, e.g., 9600.\n\n6. **Configure Data Source**:\n   - Add a data source to provide the 16-bit data you want to send. You can use blocks like `Constant`, `Sine Wave`, or any other sources.\n   - Ensure the data width matches 16 bits. You can use the `Data Type Conversion` block to convert your data to `uint16` if necessary.\n\n7. **Connect Blocks**:\n   - Connect your data source block to the input of the \"Serial Transmit\" block.\n\n8. **Running the Model**:\n   - Upload a basic serial communication sketch to your Arduino using the Arduino IDE. For example:\n   ```\n   void setup() {\n     Serial.begin(9600);\n   }\n   void loop() {\n     // Your code to handle incoming serial data\n   }\n   ```\n   - Run the Simulink model to begin transmitting data to the Arduino.\n\nHere\u2019s a simple example breakdown:\n\n```matlab\nOpen Simulink and drag the following blocks into your model:\n1. Constant Block: Set to a 16-bit value like 1234.\n2. Data Type Conversion Block: Convert the constant value to uint16.\n3. Serial Transmit Block: Set COM port and baud rate.\n\nConnect:\nConstant Block -> Data Type Conversion Block -> Serial Transmit Block\n```\n\nYour Arduino should now be receiving 16-bit data continuously from Simulink.\n\nAlways ensure that the serial settings (e.g. baud rate) on both Simulink and the Arduino sketch match. This ensures reliable communication between the two.\n\n",
